13:16.184 --> 13:19.954
There is nothing
linking either of them
to that fire.

13:19.988 --> 13:24.025
So go home and
don't worry about it.

13:24.059 --> 13:26.127
Whenever people
tell me not to be
worried about something,

13:26.161 --> 13:27.895
I get worried.

13:27.930 --> 13:30.064
Yeah, your son's
a worrier, too.

13:30.098 --> 13:31.866
Were they in the lab?

13:31.900 --> 13:34.969
They were
all over the school,
she gave him a tour.

13:35.003 --> 13:37.838
No one is accusing
them of anything,

13:37.873 --> 13:39.206
it's not being
treated as arson.

13:39.241 --> 13:40.908
What were they
doing in the lab?

13:40.943 --> 13:42.877
Who knows?
There are no cameras.

13:42.911 --> 13:44.979
The cameras are
at t entrances,

13:45.013 --> 13:48.082
they don't have cameras
in each classroom.

13:48.116 --> 13:51.152
If they did,
I'd be a wealthier man.

13:51.186 --> 13:53.955
They were
roasting marshmallows
over a Bunsen burner.

13:53.989 --> 13:55.056
What?
Yeah.

13:55.090 --> 13:56.991
And an hour later, boom,

13:57.025 --> 13:59.794
the lab blows up
and the school burns down.

13:59.828 --> 14:03.064
And you're not worried.
Why is that?

14:03.098 --> 14:04.065
Because how do
you know they were

14:04.099 --> 14:07.835
roasting marshmallows
over a Bunsen burner?

14:07.869 --> 14:10.805
I overheard a conversation.

14:10.839 --> 14:12.974
Well, maybe you
overheard wrong.

14:13.008 --> 14:16.844
If Jack doesn't
know anything then
Grace doesn't know anything,

14:16.878 --> 14:18.079
and if Grace
doesn't know anything

14:18.113 --> 14:20.014
then Adrian doesn't
know anything.

14:20.048 --> 14:22.917
So Ben isn't
talking to Adrian.

14:22.951 --> 14:24.852
I didn't think he would.

14:24.886 --> 14:27.888
Maybe he did talk to Adrian
but Adrian didn't say
anything to Grace,

14:27.923 --> 14:29.156
so Grace didn't say
anything to Jack.

14:29.191 --> 14:31.125
Oh, come on,
she would say something.

14:31.159 --> 14:32.093
You know how gossip
flies in that circle.

14:32.127 --> 14:34.128
Like wildfire?

14:34.162 --> 14:35.997
It's not funny.

14:36.031 --> 14:37.999
Ben is so worried
he wants to break up with me.

14:38.033 --> 14:39.900
Oh! Yay!

14:39.935 --> 14:41.135
What?

14:41.169 --> 14:43.838
I mean, he's great
for a starter boyfriend,

14:43.872 --> 14:45.039
but you cannot keep
him as a real boyfriend.
He's a dork.

14:45.073 --> 14:48.776
I beg your pardon.
He is not a dork.

14:48.810 --> 14:50.144
Okay, he's not a dork.
He's a rich dork.
You can do better.

14:50.178 --> 14:54.148
I don't want
to do better,
I love him.

14:54.182 --> 14:57.118
Well, I can't
keep dating Jack
to get information.

14:57.152 --> 14:59.220
I don't love him.
I don't love him at all.

15:00.022 --> 15:01.956
I mean he's hot,

15:01.990 --> 15:04.025
not so hot he'd
make a lab explode and
burn down a school, but...

15:04.059 --> 15:06.827
Okay, would you drop
the fire references?

15:06.862 --> 15:08.095
Fine. Can you
just forget Ben?

15:08.130 --> 15:10.031
Forget him?
Fine. Marry him.

15:10.065 --> 15:11.999
Then you
can't testify
against each other.

15:12.034 --> 15:14.902
It's never going
to get to that,
to our testifying.

15:14.936 --> 15:16.737
This is never
going to go to court.

15:16.772 --> 15:18.005
My father would
never let that happen.

15:19.941 --> 15:20.975
Hi.

15:21.009 --> 15:22.043
I'll be right back.

15:22.077 --> 15:24.078
Where are you going?

15:24.112 --> 15:25.146
To the bathroom.

15:25.180 --> 15:27.014
No, you can't.
We have company.

15:27.049 --> 15:28.082
So I'll just
go home and go
to the bathroom then.

15:28.116 --> 15:30.051
You can't do that either.
Just stay in here.

15:30.085 --> 15:32.920
I'll let you know
when you can come out.
Cross your legs.

15:35.791 --> 15:36.724
What is going on?

15:36.758 --> 15:39.126
Your boyfriend's father
is in the kitchen.

15:39.161 --> 15:41.829
Leo Boykewich
is in our kitchen?

15:41.863 --> 15:44.799
<i>That's the one.
He's talking to your father.
Mano a mano.</i>

15:44.833 --> 15:47.101
About what?
You tell me.

15:47.969 --> 15:49.904
Or you.

15:49.938 --> 15:52.807
Uh, now,
I really have to go.

15:52.841 --> 15:54.108
Talk to you later, Dylan.

15:56.178 --> 15:58.879
It's about that
stupid fire, isn't it?

15:58.914 --> 15:59.947
Probably. They sent
me out of the room.

15:59.981 --> 16:02.883
Mom!

16:02.918 --> 16:03.851
You should have
stayed in the room
and stood up for me!

16:03.885 --> 16:06.921
For Ben and me!
We didn't do anything.

16:06.955 --> 16:09.990
Of course not.
You're a very
conscientious young lady.

16:10.025 --> 16:11.725
I'm sure you
left the school
just as you found it.

16:11.760 --> 16:13.894
We did! I swear!

16:13.929 --> 16:15.062
You didn't go in
the lab for anything?

16:15.097 --> 16:18.899
We walked by it,
we stuck our head
in the door.

16:18.934 --> 16:21.802
We didn't do
anything that would
cause an explosion.

16:21.837 --> 16:22.970
If we did,
I would tell you.

16:23.004 --> 16:26.040
I know,
you're pretty good
about telling me things,

16:26.074 --> 16:28.075
except maybe
about the pot.

16:28.110 --> 16:30.010
You weren't smoking pot
in there, were you, Dylan?

16:30.045 --> 16:31.846
Mom!

16:31.880 --> 16:33.147
At school?
With all those
cameras around?

16:33.181 --> 16:36.851
What about
not at school where there
are no cameras around,

16:36.885 --> 16:37.952
are you still
smoking pot?

16:37.986 --> 16:39.820
No.

16:39.855 --> 16:41.956
Where would I get pot?

16:41.990 --> 16:45.960
Mercedes' mother is dead,
they don't give pot
prescriptions to dead people.

16:45.994 --> 16:49.830
It's such a shame
about her mom.
How's Mercedes doing?

16:49.865 --> 16:51.966
Her and her dad
aren't still smoking
whatever pot was left?

16:52.000 --> 16:55.769
No. There's no pot left.

16:55.804 --> 16:56.971
They're going
to counseling now.

16:57.005 --> 16:58.739
And no one
is smoking pot.

16:58.773 --> 17:01.876
Not them. Not Ben. Not me.

17:04.045 --> 17:06.946
I'll talk to Dylan
and ask her
about this alleged

17:06.982 --> 17:09.782
Bunsen burner business

17:09.818 --> 17:12.987
and if it's relevant
to the investigation
I'll let the police know.

17:13.021 --> 17:14.688
Will you?
I said I would.

17:14.723 --> 17:15.723
Then I imagine,
if you do that,

17:15.790 --> 17:16.991
then the police
are going to want
to talto Ben.

17:17.025 --> 17:18.925
I know that, so...

17:18.960 --> 17:22.829
Are you sure
this is something you
want me to say now?

17:22.864 --> 17:25.900
If I give the police
an excuse to blame
this on our children,

17:25.934 --> 17:28.669
they might just do that.

17:28.703 --> 17:30.104
Why don't we just
let this play itself out,

17:30.972 --> 17:32.940
see how it goes.

17:32.974 --> 17:36.677
Do you want
Ben to go to prison for
something he didn't do?

17:36.711 --> 17:37.945
He wouldn't last
two minutes in prison.

17:37.979 --> 17:39.747
Oh, and Dylan would?

17:39.814 --> 17:42.816
Dylan,
I remind you, is not 18.
I believe your son is.

17:42.851 --> 17:44.885
Then again, it could
have been Dylan who started
the fire and not Ben.

17:44.920 --> 17:48.989
I seriously doubt
Ben lit the Bunsen burner
and roasted the marshmallows.

17:49.024 --> 17:51.859
He doesn't cook.

17:51.893 --> 17:53.761
Never has.

17:53.795 --> 17:55.729
Yeah, but apparently
he likes playing
with matches.

17:55.764 --> 17:56.897
He smokes pot.
Once.

17:56.932 --> 17:58.866
That's what they all say.

17:58.900 --> 17:59.767
No one gets
caught the first time.

18:01.736 --> 18:01.769
Almost no one.

18:05.040 --> 18:08.742
If someone had eaten
a rancid steak from
Boykewich International,

18:08.777 --> 18:10.711
you'd know how to
handle that, right?

18:10.745 --> 18:13.647
Well this is my territory,
this is security.

18:13.682 --> 18:16.050
I know what to do here.
We wait this out.

18:21.756 --> 18:25.726
We do not
have rancid steak

18:25.760 --> 18:26.727
at Boykewich International.

18:30.447 --> 18:30.447
+

18:47.678 --> 18:48.678
Ethan?

18:49.713 --> 18:50.613
It's Ethan, right?

18:50.647 --> 18:54.784
Yeah. You're Ben?
Ben Boykewich?

18:54.818 --> 18:56.752
That's your house?

18:56.787 --> 18:59.355
I thought
you had money.

18:59.389 --> 19:00.690
That's Adrian's parents' house

19:00.724 --> 19:03.592
and anyone
who still has a house
in this economy has money.

19:03.627 --> 19:06.562
What are you
doing out here?

19:06.596 --> 19:10.733
Oh. Big pow wow
with Ricky's mothers and
Amy's mother and her dad.

19:10.767 --> 19:13.602
His mother is
my foster mother, Margaret.

19:13.637 --> 19:16.405
She dragged me here,
I'm not allowed to
be home alone.

19:16.440 --> 19:18.708
And what is this
pow wow about?

19:18.742 --> 19:21.610
I don't know.

19:21.645 --> 19:24.413
I begged her to
let me stay out here,

19:24.448 --> 19:26.415
I can't take any more
family dramas after what
I've been through, you know.

19:27.718 --> 19:29.652
Is Amy okay?

19:29.686 --> 19:32.655
Like I told you,
I don't really know.

19:32.689 --> 19:35.424
I think maybe
she and Ricky
eloped last night.

19:35.459 --> 19:38.427
You think
maybe they eloped?

19:38.462 --> 19:41.430
What?
Yeah. Maybe.

19:41.465 --> 19:42.665
And that's why
everyone is here?

19:42.699 --> 19:44.800
That's why
everyone is here.

19:44.835 --> 19:49.405
They're waiting for
them to come by and get
the kid and find out.

19:49.439 --> 19:51.774
Kind of ambush them.
Or surprise them
or something.

19:51.808 --> 19:55.511
Something like?
Are they having
a reception or anything?

19:55.545 --> 19:56.779
A what?
You know, like a party.

19:56.813 --> 20:01.550
For when they get home
from their stupid wedding.
(LAUGHS)

20:01.585 --> 20:03.419
You know what,
I don't even know why
I'm even asking you about it,

20:03.453 --> 20:06.655
none of my business.

20:06.690 --> 20:08.524
I'll see you when
school starts next week.

20:13.563 --> 20:14.597
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

20:15.465 --> 20:16.565
Come on in!

20:25.709 --> 20:28.577
Hey, long time, no see.

20:28.612 --> 20:30.513
How are you?

20:30.547 --> 20:31.647
I'm well
thank you, and you?

20:31.681 --> 20:34.683
I'm well, thank you.
And you?

20:34.718 --> 20:36.485
You already
asked me that.

20:36.787 --> 20:38.654
And?
And...

20:39.890 --> 20:41.791
You look a little pale.

20:41.825 --> 20:43.726
Sunscreen.

20:43.760 --> 20:46.796
And I just heard that

20:46.830 --> 20:48.631
Amy and Ricky eloped.

20:48.665 --> 20:50.766
No kidding. Huh.

20:50.801 --> 20:52.468
I kind of
thought they might.

20:52.502 --> 20:52.535
I didn't.

20:54.571 --> 20:56.539
Well, uh, sit down.

20:56.873 --> 20:57.873
Let's talk.

20:58.742 --> 21:00.409
I, uh...

21:00.444 --> 21:03.412
I don't know
if this is, uh...

21:03.447 --> 21:05.448
This is a good time...

21:05.482 --> 21:06.682
...to talk.

21:06.716 --> 21:07.516
Ben! Ben!

21:10.620 --> 21:12.521
How's the gay life
treating you?

21:12.556 --> 21:14.824
Fine. How's Kathleen?

21:15.759 --> 21:17.693
Fine.

21:17.727 --> 21:19.495
Please tell me that
you didn't tell her

21:19.529 --> 21:20.963
that we think
Amy and Ricky
ran off and got married.

21:20.997 --> 21:22.765
I didn't tell her that
we think Amy and Ricky
ran off and got married.

21:22.799 --> 21:25.434
Good.

21:25.469 --> 21:26.535
Because no one
should know until we know.

21:26.570 --> 21:28.571
We should be
the first to know.

21:28.605 --> 21:30.506
I doubt we'll be
the first to know
if they got married.

21:30.540 --> 21:31.674
I'm sure Amy's
going to tell Madison
and Lauren before us.

21:31.708 --> 21:33.642
She better not.

21:33.677 --> 21:34.743
I don't know for sure
she'll tell them,
I'm just guessing.

21:34.778 --> 21:36.512
Based on what
you and I did.

21:36.546 --> 21:38.514
You and I ran off
and didn't get married.

21:38.548 --> 21:39.582
We did the second
time we ran off.

21:40.617 --> 21:42.651
Yeah.
"Yeah."

21:42.686 --> 21:44.487
You didn't think
it was so "yeah"
when we got married.

21:44.521 --> 21:46.455
You were excited about it.
Or so I thought.

21:46.490 --> 21:47.756
Don't start, okay?

21:47.791 --> 21:50.759
Oop. Somebody's
up from their nap.
I'll go check on Robie.

21:50.794 --> 21:53.629
Yeah, you should
go check on Robie.
He's your kid too, you know.

21:53.663 --> 21:55.431
Didn't you just
leave Robie with me

21:55.465 --> 21:56.765
when you went
gallivanting off in
gay Paris?

21:56.800 --> 21:58.534
Shut up.

21:58.568 --> 22:00.703
Nice. Don't forget
we have company.

22:00.737 --> 22:02.471
Are they like that
all the time?

22:03.707 --> 22:06.709
Pretty much. Yeah.

22:06.743 --> 22:11.480
Well, it's probably a good
thing they are already
divorced and living apart.

22:11.515 --> 22:15.451
That constant bickering
is not good for children.

22:15.485 --> 22:19.588
I hope Amy
is not going to be
like that with our Ricky.

22:19.623 --> 22:20.389
I know.

22:22.592 --> 22:25.494
You know,
I don't know

22:25.529 --> 22:29.698
if it's a good idea
for John to be around
George and Anne so often.

22:29.733 --> 22:32.501
I mean, I'm going
to talk to Ricky

22:32.536 --> 22:34.603
about leaving him
with me more often.

22:34.638 --> 22:38.541
Well, I can babysit John.
I do just fine with him.

22:38.575 --> 22:39.708
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

22:39.743 --> 22:41.443
As long as he's asleep.

22:41.478 --> 22:42.745
I'm sure you do.
I'm just saying

22:42.779 --> 22:44.446
they should
call on me more often.

22:44.481 --> 22:45.648
Why? 'Cause you're
better than me?

22:45.682 --> 22:47.550
(SIREN WAILING)

22:47.584 --> 22:49.385
Where's Ethan?
In the car.

22:49.419 --> 22:50.519
Did you crack the windows?

22:53.868 --> 22:53.868
+

22:57.546 --> 22:59.614
He fainted,
he just fainted.

22:59.648 --> 23:01.516
I don't think there's
anything wrong with him.

23:01.550 --> 23:02.884
He didn't even
hit the ground hard,

23:02.918 --> 23:03.852
his knees buckled
and he just crumpled
onto the floor.

23:03.886 --> 23:06.588
Did you call his dad?

23:06.622 --> 23:07.589
He doesn't want me
to call his dad.

23:07.623 --> 23:08.857
And he's over 18, so...

23:08.891 --> 23:10.859
Yeah, call him
after they wheel him
out of here.

23:10.893 --> 23:12.794
Are you sure
you need to go
to the hospital?

23:12.828 --> 23:14.562
Don't you want
to just let this guy
drive you home?

23:14.597 --> 23:15.697
I want to go
to the hospital.

23:15.731 --> 23:18.767
I'm in no condition
to go home.

23:18.801 --> 23:21.636
And my throat hurts,
I can't talk anymore.

23:21.670 --> 23:23.605
All right.

23:23.639 --> 23:24.205
Maybe one of us
should ride with him.

23:24.240 --> 23:27.575
Yeah, one of us should.

23:27.610 --> 23:29.644
You know, you go ahead.
I've got some things
going on at the house.

23:29.678 --> 23:30.812
Oh, yeah, I heard.

23:30.846 --> 23:32.781
So, kids tied
the knot, huh?

23:34.550 --> 23:35.717
That's what I heard.

23:35.751 --> 23:37.652
I wish everyone
would just mind
their own business.

23:37.686 --> 23:39.654
You'd have a better chance of
shutting down the Internet.

23:39.688 --> 23:40.722
What's Ben doing
over here anyway?

23:40.756 --> 23:42.824
He and Adrian
getting back together?

23:42.858 --> 23:44.559
Why should I
mind my own business
if no one else does?

23:49.665 --> 23:51.800
Come on. Come on.
come on, come on,

23:52.668 --> 23:53.468
Grace! Pick up!

23:53.502 --> 23:56.871
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

23:56.906 --> 23:59.607
Hello, Adrian.
I hope you're
having a blessed day.

23:59.642 --> 24:01.075
What?
Thank you for calling,

24:01.110 --> 24:04.579
but as I told you,
I just think it's best
if we're not friends, so...

24:04.613 --> 24:06.714
I can't really
talk right now.

24:06.749 --> 24:09.617
Yeah, you can.
Amy and Ricky eloped.

24:09.652 --> 24:10.852
Really? Did you get that
from a reliable source?

24:10.886 --> 24:13.621
Uh, yeah, my dad.

24:13.656 --> 24:15.790
Damn it, why am I...

24:15.825 --> 24:19.594
Sorry. I'm struggling to
get back on the path,

24:19.628 --> 24:21.596
I strayed
a little bit too far.

24:21.630 --> 24:22.864
And for too long.

24:22.898 --> 24:24.833
You're not going to
play that religion card
again, are you?

24:24.867 --> 24:28.503
'Cause I know you.

24:28.537 --> 24:29.838
And I know you
get religious whenever
it's convenient like...

24:30.873 --> 24:33.608
Oh, my God!

24:33.642 --> 24:35.844
You think
you're going to hell
because we kissed?

24:35.878 --> 24:36.778
<i>Is that why you're
a Christian again?</i>

24:36.812 --> 24:39.781
That might have
something to do with it.

24:39.815 --> 24:42.584
But also, I just realized
how messed up my life was

24:42.618 --> 24:43.751
when I stopped
giving myself over
to a higher power.

24:43.786 --> 24:45.687
(DISCONNECTS)

24:53.629 --> 24:54.896
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

24:59.768 --> 25:02.537
Hey, Grace.

25:02.571 --> 25:03.538
<i>GRACE:    Hey, I have
really big news.</i>

25:03.572 --> 25:05.640
Oh, good.
Because Raven's on
her way over here

25:05.674 --> 25:07.709
and I love it when
I have information
that she wants.

25:07.743 --> 25:09.577
So I'm supposed to
give you information that
you can barter for sex?

25:09.612 --> 25:11.613
Yeah. Remember.
Judge not.

25:11.647 --> 25:14.716
Fine.
Amy and Ricky eloped.

25:14.750 --> 25:16.584
<i>Oh, I know.
Tom told me.</i>

25:16.619 --> 25:18.486
She's not pregnant
again, is she?

25:18.520 --> 25:19.487
'Cause that
would be big news.
And worth a lot.

25:19.521 --> 25:21.823
Tom? Tom told you?

25:21.857 --> 25:23.658
Now Tom knows
things before I do!

25:23.692 --> 25:24.592
(DISCONNECTS)

25:26.762 --> 25:29.864
I don't know if
that Christian thing
is going to stick.

25:29.899 --> 25:31.766
How did you know that
Amy and Ricky got married?

25:31.800 --> 25:34.602
I heard it from
dad number three.

25:34.637 --> 25:36.437
Kathleen said
not to tell anyone

25:36.472 --> 25:37.405
because we didn't
really know for sure.

25:37.439 --> 25:39.707
I'm not just anyone!
I'm your sister, Tom!

25:39.742 --> 25:40.608
And I'm your half-sister!

25:40.643 --> 25:45.580
I like the
sound of half-sister.

25:45.614 --> 25:49.550
It's like
half-woman, half-man.

25:49.585 --> 25:51.819
Half-sister,
half-brother.

25:51.854 --> 25:53.855
God help me,
I want to slap
both of you!

25:53.889 --> 25:57.692
I'll slap you.
I am not a Christian.

25:57.726 --> 26:00.495
Well, I'm not
half-man, half-woman.

26:00.529 --> 26:01.596
It sounds like
you're making some
sort of bad joke

26:01.630 --> 26:04.632
about some of the members
of the LGBTQ community.

26:04.667 --> 26:10.538
No. I'm making a joke
about you personally.

26:10.572 --> 26:12.607
