I think she thinks
you didn't have a wedding

38:29.736 --> 38:31.904
because you didn't want
her to bring a date or
something crazy like that.

38:31.939 --> 38:35.575
Maybe I didn't want
you to bring a date.

38:35.609 --> 38:37.777
Really?
You don't like Kathleen?

38:37.811 --> 38:40.713
No, no, I like her,

38:40.747 --> 38:43.883
but Dad,
honestly, a wedding?

38:43.917 --> 38:46.819
With Mom and her date
and you and your date,

38:46.854 --> 38:49.722
no matter who
either of you bring,
it would just be awkward.

38:49.756 --> 38:50.590
And then there's
my group of friends,

38:50.624 --> 38:54.627
Ben and his new girlfriend,

38:54.661 --> 38:56.596
Adrian and
whoever she's with,

38:56.630 --> 38:59.665
Grace and Jack
and Jack and Madison
and... (SCOFFS)

38:59.700 --> 39:00.700
I just started
thinking about it

39:00.734 --> 39:02.768
and my wedding should be
about me and my date.

39:02.803 --> 39:04.570
And it was.

39:04.605 --> 39:05.771
Yeah.

39:05.806 --> 39:07.740
I'm very proud
of you. And Ricky.

39:07.774 --> 39:07.840
Thanks.

39:10.744 --> 39:13.613
And thank you
for saying all those
nice things about us.

39:13.647 --> 39:15.648
Meant every word I said.

39:15.682 --> 39:17.817
And here's
something I didn't say.

39:17.851 --> 39:21.621
Being a teenage mother
is still frowned upon
in this country.

39:21.655 --> 39:23.623
People accept
that it happens

39:23.657 --> 39:24.724
but people judge
everyone involved
when it happens.

39:24.758 --> 39:26.759
People look at you,
they see the kid,

39:26.793 --> 39:29.562
they see you don't have
a ring on your finger,

39:29.596 --> 39:31.564
they judge you,
and they judge Ricky,

39:31.598 --> 39:32.865
and they feel
sorry for John.

39:32.900 --> 39:35.801
And as your father,
that hurts me.

39:35.836 --> 39:37.670
And this
doesn't take away
any of the indignities

39:37.704 --> 39:39.906
you've suffered over
the past few years,

39:39.940 --> 39:41.941
but it makes life better,

39:41.975 --> 39:43.910
for you and your husband

39:43.944 --> 39:46.012
and your family
and our family.

39:46.980 --> 39:49.916
Aw, Dad, I know.

39:51.818 --> 39:53.920
And I know that I have
caused you a lot of trouble

39:53.954 --> 39:55.888
and a lot of
heartache, but...

39:55.923 --> 39:58.824
But today is a new day.

39:58.859 --> 40:01.794
Yesterday was the
first day of the rest of
your life, Mrs. Underwood.

40:01.828 --> 40:02.995
(CHUCKLING)

40:07.734 --> 40:10.736
Let's go.
The doctor said there's
nothing wrong with you.

40:12.039 --> 40:13.906
Not buying it, Ben.

40:15.876 --> 40:19.745
I don't
feel very well.
I collapsed.

40:19.780 --> 40:20.880
At what point
in the conversation
did you collapse?

40:20.914 --> 40:23.015
Before or after
a confession?

40:27.054 --> 40:28.921
We didn't really talk.

40:28.956 --> 40:32.592
Yeah.
You're good at that,
at not talking.

40:32.626 --> 40:33.960
And I don't want
to talk to you here,

40:33.994 --> 40:36.662
where we might
be overheard, I want to
talk to you at home.

40:38.832 --> 40:40.633
I went to see
Dylan's father today.

40:41.702 --> 40:42.868
Oh, God.
Yeah.

40:42.903 --> 40:44.971
No kidding around, Benjamin,
let's get out of here.

40:51.745 --> 40:53.846
We were in the lab.

40:53.880 --> 40:54.747
We lit the Bunsen burner.

40:54.781 --> 40:59.144
We roasted marshmallows
and made s'mores.

